= Robotrek (SNES) - Known Glitches =

This page documents known bugs and glitches in Robotrek.

== Beneficial Glitches ==

=== Item Duplication Glitch ===

'''Discovered:''' Early 2000s

'''Method:'''
# Have exactly 1 of an item in your inventory
# Enter battle and use the item
# Reset the game during the item use animation
# Reload save - item may not be consumed but effect applied

'''Notes:''' Works inconsistently, timing-dependent.

=== Infinite Money Exploit ===

'''Method:'''
# Invent an item with materials
# Sell the invented item
# If you have the Lucky Charm equipped, materials have a chance to not be consumed
# Repeat for infinite money

'''Notes:''' Only works with certain material combinations.

=== Fast Leveling Glitch ===

'''Method:'''
# Fight enemies near Rococo after Chapter 2
# During battle, if you defeat an enemy while your robot is being repaired
# The EXP may be calculated multiple times

'''Notes:''' Difficult to reproduce reliably.

== Negative Glitches ==

=== Save Corruption ===

'''Trigger:''' Saving during certain event sequences

'''Symptoms:'''
* Save file becomes unloadable
* Player position corrupted
* Story flags reset

'''Prevention:'''
* Save only at inns or designated save points
* Avoid saving during or immediately after boss fights
* Keep backup saves in different slots

=== Softlock - Volcano Event ===

'''Location:''' Choco Volcano, Chapter 2

'''Trigger:''' Leaving the volcano before completing the boss fight after triggering the event

'''Result:''' Cannot re-enter volcano, cannot progress story

'''Fix:''' None - must restart from earlier save

=== Invisible Wall Glitch ===

'''Location:''' Various maps

'''Description:''' Player can get stuck behind invisible collision boundaries

'''Prevention:''' Avoid walking into corners rapidly

=== Robot Part Swap Crash ===

'''Trigger:''' Rapidly swapping robot parts during battle

'''Result:''' Game freeze

'''Prevention:''' Wait for animations to complete before swapping

== Text Display Bugs ==

=== Name Overflow ===

'''Description:''' Using 8 characters for player name can cause display issues in some text boxes

'''Example:''' Name extends into adjacent text areas

=== Dialog Skip Bug ===

'''Description:''' Rapidly pressing buttons during text can skip important dialog flags

'''Result:''' Story events may not trigger properly

== Battle System Bugs ==

=== Critical Hit Overflow ===

'''Description:''' Extremely high damage values can overflow to small numbers

'''Trigger:''' Maximum stats + critical hit + weakness = damage > 65535

'''Result:''' Damage wraps to low value (displayed correctly but wrong damage dealt)

=== Speed Tie Glitch ===

'''Description:''' When player and enemy have identical speed values

'''Behavior:''' Turn order becomes unpredictable, may favor enemy

=== Status Effect Stacking ===

'''Description:''' Some status effects can stack incorrectly

'''Example:''' Multiple poison effects from different sources

'''Result:''' Either no damage or excessive damage per turn

== Inventory Bugs ==

=== 99 Stack Overflow ===

'''Description:''' Obtaining item #100 when stack is at 99

'''Behavior:''' Item counter wraps to 0, items lost

=== Empty Slot Display ===

'''Description:''' Sometimes empty inventory slots display garbage data

'''Cause:''' Uninitialized memory

'''Harmless:''' Visual only, no gameplay impact

== Map/Event Bugs ==

=== NPC Collision Issues ===

'''Description:''' NPCs can block doorways permanently

'''Location:''' Various towns

'''Prevention:''' Talk to NPCs to move them

=== Treasure Chest Respawn ===

'''Description:''' Some chests respawn their contents after story events

'''Locations:'''
* Rococo Forest chest (Chapter 1 to Chapter 2)
* Research Lab chest (after boss)

'''Notes:''' Considered a feature by some players

=== Map Layer Z-Fighting ===

'''Description:''' Objects on different layers flicker

'''Cause:''' Priority bit conflicts in tilemap

== Audio Bugs ==

=== Music Loop Bug ===

'''Description:''' Some tracks have incorrect loop points

'''Affected:'''
* Battle victory theme (slight pop at loop)
* Choco town theme (brief silence)

=== Sound Effect Cutoff ===

'''Description:''' Multiple sound effects playing can cut each other off

'''Cause:''' Limited audio channels

== Version Differences ==

=== US vs Japanese (Slapstick) ===

Some bugs were fixed in the US localization:
* Save corruption less frequent
* Volcano softlock fixed in some versions
* Text overflow issues addressed

Some bugs were introduced:
* Translation timing issues
* Name length problems (shorter limit in Japanese)

